  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (394f217 2023-03-20T00:05:20.377895339Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge debug\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen an `MSTORE` op writes to a section of memory that is not word aligned (`mem_offset != x * 32`) the section of memory highlighted in the debugger's TUI window is still aligned to the word and does not reflect what section of memory is about to be changed by progressing to the next execution step.\r\n\r\nMeta: #4440 ",
